Troubleshooting

On this page

Troubleshooting Guide ​

Solve common OpenClaw issues.

Quick Diagnostics ​

Run the diagnostic command first:

bash
openclaw doctor
1

This checks:

  • Node.js version
  • OpenClaw version
  • Configuration validity
  • Provider connectivity
  • Channel status

Common Issues ​

Gateway Won't Start ​

Symptoms:

  • openclaw gateway start fails
  • "Port already in use" error

Solutions:

  1. Check if port is in use:
bash
lsof -i :3000
1
  1. Kill existing process:
bash
kill -9 <PID>
1
  1. Use different port:
bash
export OPENCLAW_PORT=3001
openclaw gateway start
1
2

Bot Not Responding ​

Symptoms:

  • Messages sent but no reply
  • Gateway shows running

Solutions:

  1. Check channel status:
bash
openclaw channel status telegram
1
  1. View channel logs:
bash
openclaw logs --channel telegram
1
  1. Restart channel:
bash
openclaw channel restart telegram
1
  1. Verify bot token is correct

API Key Errors ​

Symptoms:

  • "Invalid API key" errors
  • Authentication failures

Solutions:

  1. Verify key is set:
bash
echo $ANTHROPIC_API_KEY
1
  1. Check config references:
bash
openclaw config get providers.anthropic
1
  1. Regenerate key from provider dashboard

Rate Limiting ​

Symptoms:

  • "Rate limit exceeded" errors
  • Slow or failed responses

Solutions:

  1. Reduce message frequency
  2. Enable caching
  3. Upgrade API plan
  4. Use multiple providers
json
{
  "providers": {
    "fallback": {
      "enabled": true,
      "provider": "openai"
    }
  }
}
1
2
3
4
5
6
7
8

Memory Issues ​

Symptoms:

  • Slow performance
  • Out of memory errors

Solutions:

  1. Clear old sessions:
bash
openclaw sessions clear --older-than 7d
1
  1. Reduce history:
json
{
  "sessions": {
    "maxHistoryLength": 50
  }
}
1
2
3
4
5
  1. Restart regularly:
bash
openclaw gateway restart
1

Tool Execution Failures ​

Symptoms:

  • Tools timeout
  • Permission denied errors

Solutions:

  1. Check tool permissions:
bash
openclaw config get tools
1
  1. Increase timeout:
json
{
  "tools": {
    "exec": {
      "timeout": 60000
    }
  }
}
1
2
3
4
5
6
7
  1. Verify file permissions

Discord Permission Errors ​

Symptoms:

  • Bot can't send messages
  • Missing permissions errors

Solutions:

  1. Check bot roles in server
  2. Enable required intents in Discord Developer Portal
  3. Re-invite bot with correct permissions

WhatsApp Webhook Issues ​

Symptoms:

  • No messages received
  • Webhook verification fails

Solutions:

  1. Verify webhook URL is publicly accessible
  2. Check SSL certificate
  3. Confirm verify token matches

Log Analysis ​

View Logs ​

bash
# All logs
openclaw logs

# Follow logs
openclaw logs --follow

# Filter by level
openclaw logs --level error

# Filter by channel
openclaw logs --channel telegram

# Export logs
openclaw logs --export > debug.log

Reset & Recovery ​

Full Reset ​

bash
# Stop gateway
openclaw gateway stop

# Backup config
cp ~/.openclaw/config.json ~/config.backup.json

# Clear sessions
rm -rf ~/.openclaw/sessions/*

# Clear logs
rm -rf ~/.openclaw/logs/*

# Restart
openclaw gateway start
1

Restore from Backup ​

bash
openclaw backup restore <backup-id>
1

Getting Help ​

If issues persist:

  1. Search Issues: Check GitHub Issues

  2. Discord: Join our community

  3. Debug Mode: Run with verbose logging:

    bash
    OPENCLAW_LOG_LEVEL=debug openclaw gateway start
    1

  4. Report Bug: Include:

    • OpenClaw version
    • Node.js version
    • OS
    • Relevant logs
    • Steps to reproduce

Before Reporting

Try openclaw doctor first and include the output in your bug report!
